Fixed-Assets Investment Growing In Shanghai
SHANGHAI , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- In the first eleven months this year , fixed-assets investment in this top industrial center of China reached 126.4 billion yuan ( 15.2 billion U.S. dollars ) , a 3.4 percent rise over the same period last year .
Investment in the service sector , 84.4 billion yuan , accounted for two-thirds of the total , while that in infrastructure construction hit 39.4 billion yuan , 31.2 percent of all investment .
At the same time , investment in real estate dropped by three percent compared with the same period last year to 36.8 billion yuan .
